claim.claim-text:
1. A computer-implemented method for building analytical models with standardized virtual flat files, comprising:
creating at least one view of a database, wherein the at least one view comprises at least one database field and at least one transform, wherein the transform is based on database data; creating a virtual flat file from the at least one view, wherein the virtual flat file includes an identification data region, a product ownership data region, a behavior data region, a demographics data region, a model scores data region, and a contacts data region;
building at least one analytical model using the virtual flat file as input variables for the analytical model;
wherein the data regions of the virtual flat file comprise a complete input stream needed to perform a plurality of various customer analytical modeling wherein no additional data is required.
